						<summary>

						<p>Naṭarāja temple, north <hi rend="italic">gōpuram,</hi> left of entrance.</p>						

						<p>••• ••• ••• •••••</p>						

						<p>A Tamil verse (in <hi rend="italic">veṇbā</hi> metre). It says that the three (other) <hi rend="italic">gōpurams</hi> were those of the three kings who crown themselves and while this (the north <hi rend="italic">gōpuram</hi>) is of Teṉṉet Tīkkāḷun-tiṟattaṉ for the God Tillai-chchiṟṟambalavaṉ kūttaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
